  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Pool register entry and transfer at conveyancing on the Sunshine Coast</h1>
      <p class="lede">Selling a property on the Sunshine Coast with a pool? The Building Act 1975 (Qld) is unambiguous about who is responsible for what, and the consequences for getting it wrong reach into five-figure penalty territory. This page walks you through the QBCC pool register, the seller's exact obligations at conveyancing, how the Form 23 certificate moves with the property, and what to do if you discover the pool isn't on the register at all &mdash; common with older Caloundra, Nambour and Buderim properties bought before the 2010 statewide regulations.</p>
      <p>Pre-listing or pre-settlement inspection? <a class="cta" href="tel:+61485939966">Call +61 485 939 966</a> or email <a href="mailto:quotes@poolsafetysunshinecoast.com.au">quotes@poolsafetysunshinecoast.com.au</a>.</p>
    </div>
